analysis-only (no mocks/): the rendered apply keeps `: > /etc/nginx/.provisioned`, a
real file-redirect the PATH-shim sandbox cannot intercept (a redirect is not a PATH
lookup). The point this pins (haz-redir-as-mutation): the `:` command is a pure
builtin, but the redirect `> file` is a first-class Redir effect node — it ALWAYS
runs (a Redir is never a classify Command leaf, so it is never an elidable establish),
while the converged upstream `apt-get install -y nginx` DOES elide. dash -n + golden.
notes/199 cluster-A (redirection-as-effect).
